HollowSign is a minimalist encounter tracker built for Dungeons & Dragons 5e Dungeon Masters. It tracks dungeon turns, rolls for encounters, determines NPC/monster reactions, and logs each event with flavorful, horror-themed notes â€” all in a streamlined terminal interface.

---

## ğŸ”® Features

- â±ï¸ Tracks dungeon time in 10-minute ticks
- ğŸ² Rolls for random encounters using a custom d10 table
- ğŸ§  Adds 2d6-based reaction rolls for monster behavior
- ğŸ“œ Logs each encounter to `encounter_log.txt` with tick tracking
- âœï¸ Includes vivid, Curse of Strahd-style monster notes
- âš™ï¸ Powered by a single editable `encounters.json` file

---

## ğŸš€ How to Use

1. **Open your HollowSign project folder in VS Code**  
   (If you used GitHub Desktop, open the folder you cloned or created there.)

2. **Make sure you have Python 3 installed**  
   [Download Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/)

3. **Run the script**  
   - Open `hollow_sign.py` in VS Code  
   - Right-click anywhere in the code and choose **"Run Python File in Terminal"**

4. **Press Enter** to advance time in 10-minute dungeon turns.  
   If an encounter is triggered, it will roll a reaction and log all details.

